description:
a couple of our council members are going on exchange next summer, which means we need some people to join ASA for winter 2025🤸🏼‍♀️

all positions open for election and their selective important dates are in these slides! this is a great opportunity to join council and help finish off the year strong

all info is in the interest form linked in the bio🫶🏻 DM as always with any questions!

since we had to cancel the last photography session, we have another one for you guys lined up tomorrow<3
a U2 student has offered her services and will be in the lighting room tomorrow from 12:30-3:30 to take your headshots for free!!
the link for the sign up sheet is in the bio’s linktree- go ahead and sign up for a slot and show up at your designated time!
amazing opportunity especially since its free!! dont miss out🤸🏼‍♀️🫶🏻

the theme this semester is Moulin Rouge/ 20s glamour🍾  expect an amazing night with food, drinks, your friends and faculty🫶🏻
swipe for the inspo pinterest board as always👯‍♀️

Event details: 
- Restaurant is Viva Restaurant and Bar- address is 107 rue rachel e, montreal, H2W 1C8
- 2 glasses of wine included per person (not boyb)
- afterparty is at cave - address is 410 rue rachel e, montreal, H2J 2G8
- bring valid ID for cave

TICKETS DROP AT NOON TUESDAY🍾

to follow up on the amazing networking event last night, ASAxGASA has prepared a firm tour!!!! 

if you guys are interested in seeing how architecture firms look and operate, this is the perfect event🤸🏼‍♀️

link in bio with all the info and to register! from there the VP externals will reach out to those who registered with more info🫶🏻

take a break from studio deliverables and come get a donut this wednesday, you deserve it😌

in the mcconnell hall on the way to dispatch/gstore, from 10-4🫶🏻 

see you there!

🌟 Sip Through the Ages! 🌟
Get ready to time-travel through the best decades, one sip at a time! From the 60s groove to the 00s jams, each stop brings a new era and a new vibe!

🗓️ Date: Saturday, November 9
🕔 Crawl begins: 5 PM
👥 Teams up to 10 participants (or sign up as a free agent!)
🎟️ Tickets drop Monday, November 4, at noon
💵 $15 drinking ticket | $8 non-drinking ticket - Some food included!

Secure your spot and get your squad ready! 🕺💃

THIS TUESDAY‼️
Come to 508 to attend an amazing info session on how to make your best possible resume, professional profiles, etc🫶🏻
Then there’ll be a small “roast and toast” segment where our guest Rachel can give you live feedback on your stuff!!

With the networking event next week, you wont want to miss this opportunity! 🫣

See you all there!!!
